./* This is the manpage of the display2 script
.TH display1 8 "2018-11-04" "V1.0" "display2 man page"

.SH NAME
display2

.SH SYNOPSIS
display2 [-a] [-b] [-c] [-d] [-e]


.SH DESCRIPTION
This display2 script allows users to display information based on the option provided by them. It includes cpu core, current process priorities, total number of running processes, 
open file descriptors and maximum default number of file descriptors that can be opened by a process.



.SH OPTIONS
.IP -a
Provides information on the number of CPU cores on the system.
.IP -b
Provides information on the current process' priority i.e. the current script as a nice number.
.IP -c
Provides the total number of processes running under the current user.
.IP -d
Provides the nubmer of open file descriptors owned by the current user.
.IP -e
Provides the maximum default number of file descriptors that can be opened by a process.

.SH 
AUTHOR
Brian Nguyen s3689020
